history.content: If there are only 6 seats open now, they will almost certainly be filled before the adjustment period when the class enrollment allows sophomores to be moved into the class.  You can certainly cross your fingers but definitely have a backup plan.

Hey!

I was wondering how the process would work for CS C100 if I had a conflicting class and I am not eligible to directly enroll (I'm not a junior/senior). I tried to fill out the conflict form, but I wasn't eligible for the reserved seats.

I'm just concerned because there are like 6 seats left and I'm hoping that once it opens to all students, that I could get in more quickly.

Thanks!
